OL,3,CCould Jersey and Guernsey now have two
OL,4,Cseparate ferry service providers?
OL,6,FIn yesterday's announcement that
OL,7,FGuernsey had chosen Brittany Ferries,
OL,8,FDeputy Neil Inder, President of the
OL,9,FCommittee for Economic Development
OL,10,Fsaid: "If we do move to a Guernsey-
OL,11,Fonly service from Brittany Ferries,
OL,12,Fthe new arrangement would mean that
OL,13,Fthe way that some services operate
OL,14,Fwill be changed, but we will have the
OL,15,Fsame freight and passenger capacity
OL,16,Ffor our community, improved resilience
OL,17,Fin the fleet, and the benefit of
OL,18,FBrittany Ferries' expertise,
OL,19,Fwillingness to innovate, and
OL,20,Fcommitment to improved customer
OL,21,Fservices."
